category: THE ENGLISH PAST TENSE
category comment: 

clue: This irregular past tense verb is what I did to start our game of whist

response: dealt (led)

clue: This irregular past tense verb can mean completely tired out & exhausted

response: spent (worn)

clue: A brother"ood" of irregular past tenses is stood, understood & this, meaning "resisted"

response: withstood

clue: This word meaning "said not to do that thing" rhymes with "had" to traditionalists but with "maid" to many others

response: forbade

clue: You don't say "I brod the fish before frying it", nor "I throd the needle", so why this word meaning "stepped"?

response: trod

